ial Star Award\" at the [[iHeartRadio Music Awards]], \"Muser of the Year\" at the [[Shorty Awards]], and \"Favorite Influencer\" at the [[Your World Awards|Premios Tu Mundo]].\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Award show\n! Category\n! Result\n! {{Abbr|Ref.|Reference(s)}}\n|-\n| 2016\n| [[Teen Choice Award]]\n| Choice Muser\n| {{won}}\n| <ref>[https://variety.com/2016/film/news/teen-choice-awards-winners-2016-batman-justin-bieber-selena-gomez-pretty-little-liars-deadpool-1201827393/ \"Teen Choice Awards Winners 2016: Complete List\"]. ''Variety''. July 31, 2016.</ref>\n|-\n| 2016\n| [[Streamy Awards]]\n| Breakout Creator\n| {{nom}}\n| rowspan=\"2\" |<ref name=\"Streamy Awards\">[https://www.streamys.org/nominees-winners/6th-annual-nominees/ \"6th Annual Winners & Nominees\"]. ''The Streamy Awards''.</ref>\n|-\n| 2016\n| Streamy Awards\n| Entertainer of the Year\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| 2017\n| [[Teen Choice Award]]\n| Choice Muser || {{won}}\n| <ref>Rebecca Rubin and JD  Knapp (August 13, 2017). [https://variety.com/2017/tv/awards/teen-choice-awards-2017-tcas-fox-winners-list-riverdale-fifth-harmony-1202526197/ \"Teen Choice Awards 2017: \u2018Riverdale,\u2019 Fifth Harmony Shut Out Competition\"]. ''Variety''.</ref>\n|-\n| 2017\n| [[People's Choice Awards]]\n| Favorite Social Media Star\n| {{nom}}\n| <ref>[http://peopleschoice.com/2016/11/15/peoples-choice-awards-2017-full-list-of-nominees/ \"People\u2019s Choice Awards 2017: Full List Of Nominees\"]. ''People's Choice  Awards''. November 15, 2016.</ref>\n|-\n| 2017\n| [[iHeartRadio Music Awards]]\n| Social Star Award\n| {{nom}}\n| <ref>[https://www.iheart.com/content/2017-01-03-2017-iheartradio-music-awards-social-star-award-nominees/ \"2017 iHeartRadio Music Awards: Social Star Award Nominees\"]. ''iHeartRadio''. January 3, 2017.</ref>\n|-\n| 2017\n| [[Shorty Awards]]\n| Muser of the Year\n| {{nom}}\n| <ref>[http://shortyawards.com/category/9th/muser \"Muser of the Year in Social Media - Shorty Awards\"]. ''shortyawards.com''.</ref>\n|-\n| 2017\n| [[Your World Awards|Premios Tu Mundo]]\n| Favorite Influencer\n| {{nom}}\n| <ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.telemundo.com/entretenimiento/2017/07/25/mira-5-locuras-de-baby-ariel-en-su-instagram-y-muerete-de-risa-video?page=1 |title=Mira 5 locuras de Baby Ariel en su Instagram y mu\u00e9rete de risa (VIDEO) |website=Telemundo |date=July 25, 2017 |language=es}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2018\n| [[BreakTudo Awards 2018|BreakTudo Awards]]\n| Debut Music Video\n| {{nom}}\n| <ref>{{Cite web|title= BreakTudo Awards 2018: Anitta, BTS e BlackPink est\u00e3o entre os mais indicados|url = http://www.ligacaoteen.com.br/entretenimento-variedade/breaktudo-awards-2018-anitta-bts-e-blackpink-estao-entre-os-mais-indicados/105539/|work=Liga\u00e7\u00e3o Teen|access-date= October 11, 2016|language=pt}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{Official website|http://www.babyariel.com}}\n* {{IMDb name|6304812}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Ariel, Baby}}\n[[Category:2000 births]]\n[[Category:21st-century American singers]]\n[[Category:21st-century American women singers]]\n[[Category:American actresses]]\n[[Category:American child actresses]]\n[[Category:American child singers]]\n[[Category:American TikTokers]]\n[[Category:American people of Panamanian descent]]\n[[Category:American women bloggers]]\n[[Category:American bloggers]]\n[[Category:American YouTubers]]\n[[Category:Anti-bullying activists]]\n[[Category:Female TikTokers]]\n[[Category:Female YouTubers]]\n[[Category:Lifestyle YouTubers]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Florida]]\n[[Category:American people of Jewish descent]]\n[[Category:Women video bloggers]]\n[[Category:American people of Israeli descent]]\n[[Category:American people of Cuban-Jewish descent]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|American social media personality, singer and actress}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=July 2019}}\n{{Use American English|date=July 2019}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Baby Ariel\n| image              = \n| birth_name         = Ariel Rebecca Martin\n| birth_date         = {{Birth date and age|2000|11|22}}\n| birth_place        = [[Pembroke Pines, Florida]], U.S.\n| nationality        = [[United States|American]]\n| years_active       = 2015\u2013present\n| occupation         = {{flatlist|\n* [[Social media personality]]\n* Singer\n* Actress\n}}\n| website            = {{URL|babyariel.com}}\n}}\n\n'''Ariel Rebecca Martin''' (born November 22, 2000), known professionally as '''Baby Ariel''', is an American [[social media personality]], singer and actress, known for her videos on the social media platform [[musical.ly]] (now known as [[TikTok]]). She is also known for starring in the [[Disney Channel|Disney]] movie [[Zombies 2|''Zombies 2'']].\n\nIn 2017, Baby Ariel was recognized as one of the most influential people on the internet by ''[[Time (magazine)|Time]]'' magazine<ref name=\"time\">[http://time.com/4815217/most-influential-people-internet/ \"Meet the 25 Most Influential People on the Internet\"] ''Time''. June 26, 2017.</ref> and was featured on ''[[Forbes]]'' 2017 list of top entertainment influencers.<ref name=\"forbes\">[https://www.forbes.com/top-influencers/2017/entertainment/#79f8b26e3ec6 \"Top Influencers of 2017: Entertainment\"]. ''Forbes'''. Retrieved December 29, 2017.</ref><ref>[https://www.forbes.com/profile/ariel-martin/ \"Ariel Martin: Digital Star, Personality, Vlogger\"]. ''Forbes''. Retrieved December 29, 2017.</ref> She has also won the [[Teen Choice Award]] for \"Choice Muser\" in 2016 and 2017.\n\n==Career==\nIn 2015, Ariel launched an anti-bullying campaign called #ArielMovement, described by ''[[BlackBook]]'' as one of her most important endeavors.<ref name=\"BlackBook\">Ken Scrudato (December 1, 2017). [https://bbook.com/arts-culture/musical-ly-star-baby-ariels-fave-miami-hangs-debut-single-video-aww/ \"Musical.ly Star Baby Ariel\u2019s Fave Miami Hangs + Debut Single & Video 'Aww'\"]. ''BlackBook''.</ref> ''[[People (magazine)|People]]'' magazine recognized her for her support in the #HackHarassment initiative to stop [[Internet trolls]] and negativity on the Internet.<ref>Patrick Gomez (June 30, 2016).\n[http://people.com/celebrity/hannah-hart-glozell-baby-ariel-joey-graceffa-more-hackharassment-video/ \"Hannah Hart, GloZell, Baby Ariel, Joey Graceffa & More: #HackHarrasment Video\"]. ''People''.</ref>\n\nAriel signed with [[Creative Artists Agency]] in September 2016<ref name=\"billboard.com1\">Natalie Jarvey (September 27, 2017). [http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/7525574/musically-baby-ariel-signed-caa \"Musical.ly Star Baby Ariel Signs With CAA\"]. ''Billboard''.</ref> and released her debut single \"Aww\" on December 1, 2017.<ref name=\"BlackBook\" /><ref>[https://www.allmusic.com/artist/baby-ariel-mn0003690861/discography \"Baby Ariel | Album Discography\"]. ''AllMusic''.</ref><ref name=\"trackrecord\">Frida Garza (December 1, 2017). [http://trackrecord.net/musical-ly-star-baby-ariels-debut-song-is-a-bop-1820928716 \"Musical.ly Star Baby Ariel's Debut Song Is A Bop?\"]. ''Track Record''.</ref> She released her second single \"Perf\" on January 17, 2018.<ref>[https://www.broadwayworld.com/bwwmusic/article/Baby-Ariel-Unveils-New-Single-and-Video-For-PERF-20180117 \"Baby Ariel Unveils New Single and Video For PERF\"]. ''BroadwayWorld''. January 17, 2018.</ref>  On March 30, 2018, Ariel released the song \u201cSay It\u201d with Daniel Skye.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.rcarecords.com/news/daniel-skye-and-baby-ariel-release-say-it/|title=Daniel Skye and Baby Ariel release \u201cSay It\u201d|date=March 30, 2018|website=RCA Records|access-date=July 18, 2019}}</ref> She collaborated with [[EA Games]] for ''[[The Sims 4]]'', appearing as a Sim in the expansion pack ''[[The Sims 4: Get Famous]]'', released in November 2018.<ref name=\"sims 4 kotaku\">{{cite web |last1=Jackson |first1=Gita |title=New Sims Expansion Adds A Grim New Job: 'Influencer' |url=https://kotaku.com/new-sims-expansion-adds-a-grim-new-job-influencer-1829628804 |website=Kotaku |accessdate=February 22, 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn late 2018, Ariel starred in ''Baby Doll Records'', a mini-series on [[Brat (digital network)|Brat]]. In 2019, she starred in ''[[Bixler High Private Eye]]'', a  [[Nickelodeon]] television film. Later that year, it was announced that she would be appearing in the Disney Channel film ''[[Zombies 2]]'', and would portray the role of Wynter.\n\n===Press===\nIn 2016, Ariel was featured on the cover of ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' magazine alongside fellow Musical.ly personality [[Jacob Sartorius]].<ref name=\"billboard.com\">Chris Martins (October 20, 2016). [http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/magazine-feature/7549094/musically-app-lip-sync-billboard-cover \"Musical.ly's Teenage Revolution: How the Trend-Setting Lip-Sync App Is Changing the Music Industry\"]. ''Billboard''.</ref> She has appeared on ''[[60 Minutes]]''<ref name=\"cbsnews.com\">[http://www.cbsnews.com/news/60-minutes-kim-kardashian-logan-paul-social-media-influencers/ \"The Influencers\"]. ''CBS News''. October 23, 2016.</ref> and ''[[Good Morning America]]''<ref name=\"ABC\">[http://abcnews.go.com/Entertainment/baby-ariel-talks-musically-explosively-popular-app-teens/story?id=38178520 \"\u2018Baby Ariel\u2019 Talks Musical.ly, the Explosively Popular App for Teens\"]. ''ABC News''. April 6, 2016.</ref> and has been cited as a top influencer by ''[[Forbes]]'',<ref>Natalie Robehmed. [https://www.forbes.com/sites/natalierobehmed/2017/05/11/from-musers-to-money-inside-video-app-musical-lys-coming-of-age/#21bb3d96cff6 \"From Musers To Money: Inside Video App Musical.ly's Coming Of Age\"]. ''Forbes''.</ref><ref>[https://www.forbes.com/video/5392564088001/ \"What Is a Social Media Influencer? - The Business of Influence, Ep. 1\"]. ''Forbes''.</ref><ref>[https://www.forbes.com/video/5434740947001 \"The Future Landscape of Social Media - The Business of Influence, Ep. 6\"]. ''Forbes''</ref> ''[[People (magazine)|People]]'',<ref>[http://people.com/social-media-stars/baby-ariel-overnight-fame-social-media-superstar/ \"Social Media Superstar Baby Ariel on Her Overnight Fame: \u2018It Hasn\u2019t Always Been Easy\u2019\"]. ''People''. January 19, 2017.</ref> and ''[[USA Today]]''.<ref>[https://www.usatoday.com/story/tech/talkingtech/2017/06/21/instagrammers-getting-rich-advertisers-target-gen-z/103028664/ \"Instagrammers are getting rich as advertisers target Gen-Z\"]. ''USA Today''.</ref>\n\nAriel was profiled in ''[[Fast Company (magazine)|Fast Company,]]''<ref>[https://www.fastcompany.com/person/ariel-baby-ariel-martin \"Ariel \"Baby Ariel\" Martin: Latest News, Work, Videos, Photos on Fast Company\"]. ''Fast Company''.</ref><ref>[https://www.fastcompany.com/3064054/the-social-mediators-7-young-social-stars-share-their-rules-for-engag \"The Social Mediators: 7 Young Social Stars Share Their Rules For Engagement\"]. ''Fast Company''. October 17, 2016.</ref> ''[[Business Insider]]'',<ref>[http://www.businessinsider.com/who-is-baby-ariel-2016-6 \"This 15-year-old social media star has millions of fans who follow her crazy lip-syncing videos\"]. ''Business Insider''.</ref> and ''[[Seventeen (American magazine)|Seventeen Magazine]]''.<ref>[http://www.seventeen.com/celebrity/music/news/a47943/baby-ariel-has-already-recorded-two-songs/ \"Musical.ly Star Baby Ariel Will Be Dropping Her Own Music\"]. ''Seventeen'', June 12, 2017.</ref> Other mentions include [[CNN]],<ref>Sherisse Pham (November 16, 2016). [http://money.cnn.com/2016/11/16/technology/musically-success-china-shanghai-baby-ariel/index.html \"How China's musical.ly cracked the code for success in the U.S.\"]. ''CNNMoney''.</ref> ''[[Rolling Stone]]'',<ref>Brittany Spanos (February 27, 2017). [https://www.rollingstone.com/music/features/how-teen-craze-musically-got-too-big-for-pop-to-ignore-w468324 \"How Teen Craze Musical.ly Got Too Big for Pop to Ignore\"]. ''Rolling Stone''.</ref> ''[[Huffington Post]]'',<ref>Juliet Schroder (October 1, 2016). [http://www.huffingtonpost.com/juliet-schroder/get-to-know-musicallys-bi_b_12275448.html \"Get to Know Musical.ly's Biggest Star Baby Ariel\"].</ref> Tubefilter,<ref>[http://www.tubefilter.com/2017/06/28/baby-ariel-joanne-the-scammer-time-magazine-influential-internet/?mc_cid=45377d7a20&mc_eid=8a9d9c35d7 \"Baby Ariel, Joanne The Scammer Named Most Influential On The Internet By 'Time' - Tubefilter\"]. June 28, 2017.</ref> ''[[Paper Magazine]]'',<ref>[http://www.papermag.com/musical-ly-star-baby-ariel-on-handling-sudden-fame-and-her-favorite-ar-2461469565.html \"Musical.ly Sensation Baby Ariel on Handling Sudden Fame and Her Favorite Artist to Lip Sync\"]. ''Paper'', July 18, 2017.</ref> RAW,<ref>[http://rawpages.com/2017/08/baby-ariel-interview/ \"Baby Ariel Talks New Original Music, WCW Kylie Jenner & MCM Cameron Dallas\"]. ''RAW''.</ref> and Wonderwall.<ref>[http://www.wonderwall.com/celebrity/social-media/meet-baby-ariel-the-number-one-muser-on-musically-1913702.article \"Meet Baby Ariel, the number one muser on video sharing social network musical.ly\"]. March 25, 2016.</ref>\n\n==Personal Life==\nMartin was born to a Panamanian father and a Cuban-Israeli mother.<ref>https://www.us.hola.com/celebrities/20200314fljxfyeeif/baby-ariel-disney-zombies-selena-gomez-interview%3fviewas=amp</ref><ref>https://m.youtube.com/watch?v=Z9vWv93LHZg</ref>\n\n==Discography==\n====Singles====\n{| class=\"wikitable unsortable\"\n|-\n! Title\n! Date\n! Album\n! Video Link\n|-\n| Aww\n| December 1, 2017\n| Non-album single\n|[https://m.youtube.com/watch?v=rCnU-IDcnnI Click Here]\n|-\n| Perf\n| January 7, 2018\n| Non-album single\n|[https://m.youtube.com/watch?v=W-Z1-VJj-GE Click Here]\n|-\n| Say It (with Daniel Skye)\n| March 30, 2018\n| Non-album single\n|[https://m.youtube.com/watch?v=hMgH4gMkraM Click Here]\n|-\n| Gucci On My Body\n| June 14, 2018\n| Non-album single\n|[https://m.youtube.co