o language|Amo]]\n|\n|\n|[[Plateau State|Plateau]]\n|Active\n|-\n|Anaguta \n|\n|\n|[[Plateau State|Plateau]]\n|Active\n|-\n|[[Anang]]\n|\n|\n|[[Akwa Ibom State|Akwa Ibom]]\n|Active\n|-\n|[[Angas languages|Angas]]\n|\n|\n|[[Bauchi State|Bauchi]], [[Jigawa State|Jigawa]], [[Plateau State|Plateau]]\n|Active\n|-\n|Ankwei \n|\n|\n|[[Plateau State|Plateau]]\n|Active\n|-\n|Anyima \n|\n|\n|[[Cross River State|Cross River]]\n|Active\n|-\n|[[Arabic]]\n|[[Chadian Arabic]] also known as [[Chadian Arabic|Shuwa Arabic]]\n|\n|[[Borno State|Borno]] by [[Baggara|Baggara Arabs]]\n|Active\n|-\n|Attakar \n|Ataka\n|\n|Kaduna\n|Active\n|-\n|Auyoka\n|Auyokawa, Auyakawa, Awiaka\n|\n|Jigawa\n|Active\n|-\n|[[Awori]]\n|\n|\n|Lagos, Ogun\n|Active\n|-\n|[[Ayu]]\n|\n|\n|Kaduna\n|Active\n|-\n|[[Babur]]\n|\n|\n|Adamawa, Bomo, Taraba, Yobe\n|Active\n|-\n|[[Bacama language|Bachama]] \n|\n|\n|[[Adamawa State|Adamawa]]\n|Active\n|-\n|Bachere \n|\n|\n|Cross River\n|Active\n|-\n|[[Bada]]\n|\n|\n|Plateau\n|Active\n|-\n|[[Bade language|Bade]]\n|\n|\n|Yobe\n|Active\n|-\n|Bahumono \n|\n|\n|Cross River\n|Active\n|-\n|Bakulung \n|\n|\n|Taraba\n|Active\n|-\n|[[Bali language (Adamawa)|Bali]]\n|\n|\n|Taraba\n|Active\n|-\n|[[Bambora]]\n|Bambarawa\n|\n|Bauchi\n|Active\n|-\n|[[Bambuko]]\n|\n|\n|Taraba\n|Active\n|-\n|[[Banda languages|Banda]]\n|Bandawa\n|\n|Taraba\n|Active\n|-\n|[[Banka language|Banka]]\n|Bankalawa\n|\n|Bauchi\n|Active\n|-\n|[[Banso]]\n|Panso\n|\n|Adamawa\n|Active\n|-\n|[[Bara language (Nigerian)|Bara]]\n|Barawa\n|\n|Bauchi\n|Active\n|-\n|[[Barke]]\n|\n|\n|Bauchi\n|Active\n|-\n|[[Baruba]]\n|Barba\n|\n|Niger\n|Active\n|-\n|Bashiri\n|Bashirawa\n|\n|Plateau\n|Active\n|-\n|[[Basa languages|Basa]]\n|\n|\n|Kaduna, Kogi, Niger, Plateau\n|Active\n|-\n|[[Bata language|Batta]] \n|\n|\n|[[Adamawa State|Adamawa]]\n|Active\n|-\n|Baushi \n|\n|\n|Niger\n|Active\n|-\n|[[Baya language|Baya]]\n|\n|\n|Adamawa\n|Active\n|-\n|[[Bekwarra language|Bekwarra]]\n|\n|\n|Cross River\n|Active\n|-\n|[[Bele language|Bele]]\n|Buli